 &lt;a class="text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#bluetti-charger-1-alternator-charger-review-for-camper-vans" aria-label="Anchor"&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;
 &lt;/span&gt;
 
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After seven years full-time in a 2017 Dodge ProMaster 2500, I can tell you this: alternator charging is one of the most underrated upgrades in van life. Solar is excellent, but weather and parking conditions can cut your harvest hard. A good &lt;strong&gt;alternator charger for camper van&lt;/strong&gt; use fills that gap and keeps your power plan stable. I tested the Bluetti Charger 1 in real driving workflows, not just in ideal install demos.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Bluetti Elite 200 V2 Power Station Review for Van Life</title><link>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/gear/bluetti-elite-200-v2-power-station-review/</link><pubDate>Fri, 20 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://gwinn092.github.io/van.affiliation/gear/bluetti-elite-200-v2-power-station-review/</guid><description>&lt;h1 class="relative group"&gt;Bluetti Elite 200 V2 Power Station Review for Van Life
